start-details:

h2:Terminate EMR cluster

This node terminates the EMR cluster.

end-details:

start-examples:

h2: Terminate EMR JobFlow Examples

h4: Example of Terminating an EMR Cluster

{
"ClusterId": "j-1234567890ABCDE",
"aws_conn_id": "aws_default",
"Name": "TerminateCluster",
"trigger_rule": "all_success"
}

h4: Explanation
* This example demonstrates how to terminate a specific EMR cluster by providing its Cluster ID and using the default AWS connection ID.

h4: Usage
* Task ID: "terminate_emr_task"
* Cluster ID: j-1234567890ABCDE
* Trigger Rule: all_success

h4: Example of Terminating an EMR Cluster Without Specifying Cluster ID

{
"Name": "TerminateCluster",
"aws_conn_id": "aws_default",
"trigger_rule": "all_success"
}

h4: Explanation
* This example shows how to terminate an EMR cluster without specifying the Cluster ID. The operator will attempt to retrieve the Cluster ID from a previous EMR creation task.

h4: Usage
* Task ID: "terminate_emr_task"
* Trigger Rule: all_success

end-examples: